      "description": "Solid budget-friendly driver/project with good bones and plenty of usable life left. Engine starts up, pulls cleanly, and the transmission does its job, making this a great candidate for someone who wants affordable transportation or a platform to sort and improve over time. Not a showroom car, but it has the kind of mechanical straightforwardness that makes it appealing: honest wear, practical utility, and strong value for the money. If you want inexpensive entry into ownership with upside for the next owner, this one is worth a look.",
